<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Major Banks Raise Key Interest Rates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Major Banks in Hong Kong
decided here today that they will raise their key rates by 25
basis points with effect from March 27.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made shortly after the recent increase in the
Federal Funds rate of 0.25 percent by the U.S. Federal Reserve and
the increase in the Liquidity Adjustment Facility rates by the
Hong Kong Monetary Authority by 0.25 percent.
</P>
<P>
Standard Chartered Bank announced that its best lending rate
will be increased by 0.25 percent to 8.75 percent per annum and
that its standard mortgage rate will also be increased by 0.25
percent, with both changes to take effect from March 27, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Hang Seng Bank announced that it will raise its prime lending
rate from 8.5 percent to 8.75 percent per annum, effective on
March 27.
</P>
<P>
Bank of China Hong Kong Branch announced that with effect from
March 27, its prime rate will be raised by 0.25 percent to 8.75
percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
