<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tung Chee Hwa Shows Confidence in Shanghai-HK Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Tung Chee Hwa, chief executive
of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR), said here
today that he holds full confidence in the cooperation between
Shanghai and Hong Kong to achieve common prosperity.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the Shanghai-Hong Kong Economic and Trade Forum,
Tung said that he is happy to explore closer cooperations with
Shanghai, where he was born and spent his childhood.
</P>
<P>
He said Shanghai is one of the economically strongest cities in
China, with powerful manufacturing and high-tech industries and
booming service trades. Since 1992 the city's economic growth rate
has been above the national average.
</P>
<P>
At the forum, Shanghai Deputy Mayor Chen Liangyu said that the
cooperation will definitely start a new situation in promoting
common prosperity of the two economies, adding that Hong Kong has
long been Shanghai's most important economic and trade partner.
</P>
<P>
At present, Hong Kong business people have set up more than
6,500 projects in Shanghai, which involve a total contracted
investment of 20.8 billion US dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
