<HEADLINE> Russia Gives Priority to Ties With China: Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin
today said that Russia has placed priority on developing cooperative
relations of good-neighborliness and friendship with China.
</P>
<P>
"We are looking forward to (Chinese) President Jiang Zemin's
state visit to Russia (next month), which will undoubtedly further
promote Russian-Chinese relations," Chernomyrdin told Chinese Vice
Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen, who arrived here Monday
on a four-day official visit.
</P>
<P>
He said he was glad to know that Qian had discussed all aspects
of Sino-Russian relations with President Boris Yeltsin and Foreign
Minister Yevgeny Primakov.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that the two sides will make constant efforts to
insert momentum in developing Russian-Chinese ties in an all-round
way," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Russian prime minister said that he was also looking
forward to his visit to China in late May for the second regular
meeting with Chinese Premier Li Peng.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that Li's visit to Russia at the end of last year
marked the official start of a mechanism of regular meetings
between the premiers of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Facts show that the mechanism of regular high-level meetings is
highly effective and of great significance in deepening bilateral
cooperation in various fields, especially in the economy and
trade, he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the two sides, through concerted efforts, can
attain the target of increasing bilateral trade turnover to 20
billion U.S. dollars by the end of the century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
