<HEADLINE> Kashmir Issue Top on Agenda in Pak-India Talks: FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Foreign Minister
Gohar Ayub Khan said here today Pakistan was ready to discuss all
issues including Siachin with India apart from Kashmir but Kashmir
would remain on the top of the agenda.
</P>
<P>
Talking to newsmen here about the forthcoming foreign
secretary-level talks between Pakistan and India, Gohar said that
"we would continue to talk with India to sort out issues."
</P>
<P>
Answering a question, the foreign minister said that it was
very difficult to say at the moment that any particular issue
would be solved during the talks.
</P>
<P>
"Things always move step by step," said Gohar.
</P>
<P>
He said that "I want to say very little about the talks in
order not to confuse the situation."
</P>
<P>
Pakistan wanted to settle issues with India through talks,
but, it didn't mean that "it is weak," said Gohar, adding that "in
fact, it shows our strength and confidence to come to terms with
our neighbor." 
</P>
</TEXT>
