<HEADLINE> France Stresses Emergency for Israel-Syria Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 26 (Xinhua) -- French Foreign Minister Herve de
Charette today stressed the emergency for a resumption of
negotiations between Israel and Syria and Lebanon, said French
Foreign Ministry spokesman Jacques Rummelhardt.
</P>
<P>
De Charette made the appeal during a meeting with the president
of the Lebanese parliament, Nabih Berri, who ended a three-day
visit here today after meeting with French President Jacques
Chirac and President of the French National Assembly Philippe
Seguin.
</P>
<P>
"We are worried about the degradation of Israeli-Palestinian
relations, and the persistent blockade of the (negotiation on the)
Lebanese and Syrian parts," said the spokesman, adding that France
considers it emergent for Israel to resume negotiations with both
Palestinians and Syria and Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
French negotiator in charge of the Middle East peace process
Jean-Claude Cousseran held talks with Syrian President Hafez Al
Assad Tuesday in Damascus on the situation of the peace process.
</P>
<P>
This is the second time within a few weeks for Cousseran, who
is the director of the North Africa and Middle East department of
the French Foreign Ministry, to meet the Syrian president.
</P>
</TEXT>
