<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Finnish Exports of High-Tech Products Rise in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Finland's exports of high-tech
products rose 17 percent last year to 5.06 billion U.S. dollars, a
report by the Finnish Statistics Center said today.
</P>
<P>
Exports of high-tech products accounted for 13.6 percent of the
country's total exports in 1996, compared with 12.4 percent in the
previous year.
</P>
<P>
Telecommunications equipment took the lion's share, with 66
percent of high-tech exports, up 6 percent from 1995. Exports of
computers and instruments, a main export sector, fell slightly in
1996.
</P>
<P>
The report attributed the increase in high-tech exports to the
government's support for the development of high-tech products.
</P>
<P>
Statistics showed that in 1995 the government allocated 2.3
percent of gross domestic product to the development of high-tech
products.
</P>
<P>
As for high-tech imports, the report said Finland imported 4.28
billion dollars worth of high-tech products in 1996, of which
telecommunications equipment and computers accounted for more than
65 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
