<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Traditional Chinese Art Should Be Enhanced: Jiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 26 (Xinhua) -- The development of traditional
Chinese art should be further enhanced, said President Jiang
Zemin, who visited this evening an exhibition of the late Chinese
painter Pan Tianshou at the China Art Gallery.
</P>
<P>
Looking carefully at the painter's representative works of
different periods with great interest, Jiang, who is also
Secretary-General of the Communist Party of China Central
Committee, spoke highly of the national characteristics reflected
in the works.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also expressed his hope that the art workers throughout
the country will also learn from other nations' cultural
heritages, to further promote China's art undertakings.
</P>
<P>
Regarded as one of the main founders of China's modern
educational system for traditional Chinese paintings, Pan
Tianshou, born 100 years ago, was one of the masters of
traditional Chinese paintings this century.
</P>
<P>
Experts say Pan's works have a sense of strength and the
structural beauty, and are full of the essence of life
itself. While his works fully represent the traditional way of
painting, he went beyond the traditions and created his own
understandings of art.
</P>
<P>
Some sixty works, most of which were done during the painter's
later years, were showed this time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
