<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Celebrates Independence Day today </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh celebrated its
Independence Day today amidst patriotic zeal, fanfare and fresh
vow to consolidate the hard-own independence.
</P>
<P>
The day was heralded with a 31-gun salute. The national flag
was hoisted atop all public and private buildings while the main
roads and road islands in the capital city Dhaka were decorated
with flags and lightings.
</P>
<P>
Bangladeshi President Shahabuddin Ahmed and Prime Minister
Sheikh Hasina this morning placed wreaths at the national memorial
at Savar to pay respect to the martyrs of the war.
</P>
<P>
Visiting South African President Nelson Mandela, Turkish
President Suleyman Demiral and President of the Palestinian
National Authority Yasser Arafat also laid wreaths at the memorial
early today.
</P>
<P>
In separate message on the day, the Bangladeshi president and
prime minister called for taking fresh vow to build a happy,
self-reliant and prosperous Bangladesh for the future generation.
</P>
<P>
In the morning, the prime minister addressed the nation at a
public meeting after receiving the independence torch, which
returns to the capital after touring the country beginning from
March 7.
</P>
<P>
The three visiting heads of state were also present on the
occasion and congratulated the 25th anniversary independence of
Bangladesh. 
</P>
</TEXT>
