<HEADLINE> Strong Quake Shakes Southern Japanese Island, Injuring 19 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, March 26 (Xinhua) - At least 19 people were injured as a
strong earthquake shook the southern part of Japan's southwestern
main island of Kyushu today, the Japanese Meteorological Agency said.
</P>
<P>
The quake, which struck at 5:31 p.m. local time, also damaged
buildings and disrupted train services, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
The quake measuring 6.2 on the open-ended Richter scale also
jolted a large area of the southern main island of Shikoku and the
Chugoku region in the western part of Honshu Main Island.
</P>
<P>
There was no danger of tsunami, or tidal waves, the agency
said. 
</P>
