<HEADLINE> Finland Provides Humanitarian Aid to Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Finnish Foreign Ministry decided
today to provide one million Finish Marks (about 200,000
U.S.dollars) worth of humanitarian aid to Albania to help it
overcome its current political crisis.
</P>
<P>
Pekka Haavisto, a senior official in charge of foreign aid, said
that European countries have a great responsibility in helping
Albania, which currently suffer from turmoil after a investment
scandal that brought down the government.
</P>
<P>
He expressed fear that European countries would bear the brunt
of a possible exodus of refugees from Albania if the current
crisis could not be properly handled.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Finnish Red Cross will also dispatch a medical
expert to Albania who will stay there for at least three months.
</P>
<P>
Besides Albania, Finland recently also donated half a million
marks to the Democratic People's Republic of Korea to help flood
victims and 250,000 marks to Iran following an earthquake.
</P>
</TEXT>
