<HEADLINE> Number of Cholera Victims in Somalia Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, March 26 (Xinhua) -- The number of cholera victims
is increasing in the Lower Shabelle region of Somalia.
</P>
<P>
Reports from Wanlewein District, 90 km south of Mogadishu,
said more than 300 people have died of cholera in the region
since last month.
</P>
<P>
According to Mohamed Haji Qasim, the Chairman of the newly-set
up Cholera Committee in Lower Shabelle, seven people
died of the disease yesterday in Wanlewein.
</P>
<P>
According to the committee, the World Health Organisation and
an Italian aid agency, CISP, have so far responded to the plight
of the cholera-hit people in the region. The CISP has offered 100
litters of solution to the victims of the disease, while WHO is
also offering oral rehydration solutions and essential drugs.
</P>
<P>
However, the committee said the medicines are far less than
required.
</P>
<P>
The committee urged the aid agencies to quickly intervene in
the desperate situation of the Somalia people. enditem

