<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Confers with Gore on Principles Guiding Sino-US Ties (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 26 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin told
visiting US Vice-President Al Gore here today that healthy and
stable Sino-US relations toward the 21st century should be based
on three principles: adherence to common interests,
farsightedness, and a proper handling of the Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
"In the new situation, the need for the two countries to
maintain and expand cooperation is not dwindling, but growing
continuously," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
In particular, there exist very great, cooperative potentials
for the two countries to jointly safeguard global and regional
peace, develop bilateral economic and trade ties, and promote the
growth and prosperity of the world economy, he said.
</P>
<P>
Governments of the two countries and their leaders should have
a full understanding about this. And what's more, people of both
countries should reach such a consensus.
</P>
<P>
"One should stand higher and see farther while dealing with
Sino-US relations," the Chinese President said, quoting a poem
from Wang Anshi, a well-known reformer in Song Dynasty (960-1279),
"Unafraid of floating clouds blocking eyesight, because you at the
pinnacle."
</P>
<P>
"We should dispel all interferences and noises in Sino-US
relations, stand higher and see farther, get a firm hold of the
fundamental interests of the peoples of the two countries, and
keep in mind the overall situation of bilateral relations, the
whole world situation as well as the endeavor to bring into the
21st century a prosperous, stable and peaceful world," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Concerning differences on some issues, they can be resolved on
the basis of mutual respect, non-interference in each other's
internal affairs, and equal consultations. And if some differences
cannot be resolved for the time being, the two sides can seek
common ground while reserving differences, but they cannot meddle
in the overall situation in developing relations between the two
countries, he noted.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970327.0031 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Small Private Jet Smashes Into Truck in La Guardia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, March 26 (Xinhua) -- A small private jet smashed into
a maintenance truck parked on the runway at La Guardia airport,
New York, Tuesday, forcing cancellation of flights throughout the
day in New York and at airports nationwide.
</P>
<P>
In the incident which occurred early in the morning, the small
two-engine plane, with four people on board, crashed into a white
Port Authority truck, narrowly missing two workers who had been
given clearance to change bulbs in the runway lights, said a New
York Times report today.
</P>
<P>
The incident caused the closure of the entire airport for about
one and half hour, forced the cancellation of 80 lights and
delayed the plans of thousands of passengers throughout the day in
New York and all airports nationwide. Emergency vehicles quickly
encircled the jet, spraying foam to prevent the fuel from
igniting.
</P>
<P>
Officials marveled that there were no injuries. The incident is
still under investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
