<DOCNO> XIE19970327.0032 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Confers with Gore on Principles Guiding Sino-US ties (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With regard to the proper handling of the Taiwan issue, Jiang
Zemin said that the kernel content of the three Sino-US joint
communiques is precisely one to define the guiding principle for
dealing with the issue.
</P>
<P>
The United States had made solemn commitment on the Taiwan
question. But in the history of the development of Sino-US
relations, the issue has experienced repeated hindrances, which
even undermined the process of improving and developing Sino-US
relations, he said.
</P>
<P>
"We have talked about the topic time and again, just in a hope
that it would not affect the smooth growth of Sino-US ties any
more," he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang welcomed the US Vice-President on his first trip to
China, and said that Gore has come at a time when Sino-US ties
have entered into an important period. Gore held in-depth and
friendly talks with Premier Li Peng Tuesday on Sino-US relations
and world issues of mutual concern, and both were present at the
Sino-US Forum on environment and development, Jiang added.
</P>
<P>
Jiang told Gore that "I wish your current visit will help
increase your understanding of China." Gore said that he was
pleased to have the opportunity to meet Jiang again.
</P>
<P>
On behalf of the US administration, he expressed deep grief
over the loss of Deng Xiaoping, and conveyed to Jiang the regards
of US President Clinton.
</P>
<P>
Gore said President Clinton welcomes Jiang to pay a state visit
to the United States later this year, and Jiang expressed his
thanks for this and thanked Gore for the condolences he conveyed
at the Chinese embassy in Washington after Deng's death.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin also asked Gore to forward his regards to Clinton,
adding that he is looking forward to meeting Clinton again and he
welcomes Clinton's visit to China.
</P>
<P>
"Although Comrade Deng Xiaoping has left us, we will
unswervingly advance the great cause of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics, which was initiated by him," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping had attached great importance to Sino-US
relations and had made historic and significant contributions in
forging diplomatic ties between the two countries and improving
bilateral relations, Jiang noted.
</P>
<P>
"Comrade Deng Xiaoping held a firm belief that Sino-US
relations will be improved eventually. We'll bear in mind Comrade
Deng Xiaoping's entrust, ready to make concerted efforts with the
US side to push forward the sound and steady development of
Sino-US relations," Jiang Zemin said.
</P>
</TEXT>
