<HEADLINE> EU to Enhance Support for Poor Countries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 26 (Xinhua) -- The European Union will enhance
support to heavily indebted poor countries in Africa, the Caribbean
and the Pacific (ACP).
</P>
<P>
The European Commission, EU's executive body, today adopted a
proposal for enhanced support to poor ACP nations. The proposal
was presented by Joao de Deus Pinheiro, EU commissioner for
development and external relations with ACP states.
</P>
<P>
The proposal was made in the HIPC Debt initiative, a program of
action to alleviate the debt problems of the heavily indebted poor
countries.
</P>
<P>
The initiative, endorsed at the 1996 annual meeting of the
International Monetary Fund and the World Bank in Washington , "is
a unique opportunity for the international community to assist the
poorest" countries in the world, said Pinheiro.
</P>
<P>
Under the proposal, EU would provide additional structural
adjustment assistance, financing of debt repayment and expertise
on debt management.
</P>
<P>
Pinheiro said that EU, as a major development partner of ACP
countries, has an important role to play in this initiative.
</P>
