<HEADLINE> China Will Stick to Policy of Opening, Reform: Qiao Shi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of the Standing
Committee of the National People's Congress of China, said here
today that China will stick to its policy of opening and reform.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with representatives of France's national
employers' association, the CNPF, and the France-China Committee,
Qiao said that the internal political situation of China is stable
and China's policy of opening and reform will not change.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Chinese Communist Party will hold its 15th
Congress in the latter half of this year, and it will better
implement the policies and lines that have already been decided.
</P>
<P>
He said that China is continuously improving its environment
for foreign enterprises to make investment, in order to create a
very favorable condition for carrying out economic cooperation and
exchanges with all countries of the world.
</P>
<P>
On questions concerning China's application for membership of
the World Trade Organization, Qiao said that China intends to
protect its own industry, but it does not mean that it will close
its door, because to protect China own industry falls within the
scale of the overall development of the country.
</P>
<P>
On Sino-French economic relations, Qiao said that China wishes
that Sino-French trade can be maintained with an overall balance,
and that French export products to and technological cooperation
projects with China place a greater emphasis on high technological
quality.
</P>
<P>
He said that many French enterprises are having successful
business in China because they pay great importance to the high
technological quality of their projects.
</P>
<P>
"I hope that French products have a greater competitive power.
High technological quality and great competitive power should be
the aims of all enterprises," he added.
</P>
<P>
Qiao also expressed his confidence that China and France can
achieve the goal of having greater bilateral economic cooperation
and that Sino-French friendship will develop continuously. 
</P>
</TEXT>
