<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-26 18:30 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arab Countries to Unify Actions on Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Arab foreign ministers will adopt a
unified stance on dealing with the Israeli settlement policy and
seeking international support to boost the Palestinian cause, a
senior Palestinian official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Head of the PLO Political Department Farouk Kaddoumi told
reporters that the joint Arab action strategy on the Israeli
settlement policy in Arab East Jerusalem tops the agenda of the
Arab League (AL) Council meeting scheduled for Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Other topics of the Arab foreign ministers' 107th session are
means of pooling support for the Palestinian intifada (uprising),
Palestinian refugees and the recent developments of situation on
the Palestinian lands, said Kaddoumi during a stopover here on his
way to Morocco for the Jerusalem Committee meeting.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian-Israeli relations have deteriorated as Israel went
ahead with the 6,500-unit housing project in Abu Ghneim, or Har
Homa, in East Jerusalem where Palestinians hope to create a
capital.
</P>
<P>
Israel seized East Jerusalem in the 1967 war and wants the
entire city to remain undivided under Israeli sovereignty.
</P>
<P>
In a desperate move against the Israeli settlement construction
in East Jerusalem, a militant Palestinian carried out a suicide
bombing attack in a Tel Aviv cafe last Friday, killing three women
and wounding 48 other.
</P>
<P>
This was the latest fatal incident by the Palestinians to
avenge on the Israeli building operations. Observers say more
similar attacks are feared to come.
</P>
<P>
The incidents in the occupied Palestinian territories are a
"natural reaction to Israel's repressive and provocative policies
and its continuation with building settlements," Kaddoumi said.
</P>
<P>
"What the Palestinian people are doing are self-defense and in
defense of the peace process that is crumbling," he added.
</P>
<P>
"Israel is trying to impose a new fait accompli on Jerusalem,
This attitude actually undermines stability in the region and
leads it back to violence," he added.
</P>
<P>
Following a meeting with AL Secretary General Esmat Abdel
Meguid today, the PLO official said they discussed issues to be
tabled on the AL council meeting.
</P>
<P>
Meguid has said earlier that Arab foreign ministers will take
up support of the Palestinian Intifada (uprising) as "one of the
major props against the Israeli arrogance" on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Kaddoumi is heading for Rabat to attend the Jerusalem
Committee meeting, which is expected to map out an executive
mechanism for shelving normalization with Israel.
</P>
<P>
A plan prepared by the PNA, Egypt and Saudi Arabia calls upon
all the Arab and Islamic countries to immediately freeze their
relations with Israel, withdraw from any economic or trade
projects in which Israel is a partner and suspend bilateral and
multilateral cooperation with Israel.
</P>
<P>
The plan, to be forwarded to the Rabat meeting, also urges the
establishment of a 1-billion-dollar fund to protect Islamic
holy sites in Jerusalem from being purchased by Jewish settlers.
</P>
</TEXT>
