<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Court Rejects Appeals of Three Egyptian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia's federal supreme
court announced today that it has dismissed appeals by the three
Egyptian terrorists sentenced to death for an attempt on the life
of Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak in June 1995.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia's federal high court sentenced to death in September
1996 Soufit Hassen Abdulkeni, Abdulkerim Alnadi Abduradi and
Alarabi Sadit Hafez after they were proved guilty of the
assassination attempt on President Hosni Mubarak.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ethiopian News Agency, the federal supreme
court said it has dismissed the appeals the three terrorists made
against the death penalty they were given after a thorough
examination of the case.
</P>
<P>
The terrorists in their appeals said the prosecution did not
prove that they have committed the crime and their involvement in
the assassination attempt on President Mubarak, the court said.
</P>
<P>
The terrorists, the court said, were operating according to
orders from the leadership of Gama-Al-Islamia, whose members they
are, until the time the attempt was made on the life of the
president.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the gravity of the crime they committed, they
were also responsible for the death of two individuals and the
injury two others sustained, it said.
</P>
<P>
The type of arms they used and the weapons they had in store
coupled with the highly organized criminal act was a tangible
proof to the dangerous condition, the court added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
