<HEADLINE> Egyptian Women Protest Over Israeli Settlement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, March 26 (Xinhua) -- About 50 women from the Egyptian
trade unions and political parties today gathered outside the
headquarters of the Arab League (AL) here to protest against the
Israeli building of a new Jewish neighborhood in Arab East
Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The demonstrators held banners and shouted slogans such as
"Jerusalem is Arab," demanding an emergency Arab summit
to discuss Israel's settlement policies in Arab lands.
</P>
<P>
It is the latest of a string of protests in the Egyptian
capital against the Abu Ghneim or Har Homa project and Israeli
attempts to Judaize Jerusalem, which is holy to Christians,
Muslims and Jews alike.
</P>
<P>
Cairo University students staged a two-day demonstration on
campus Monday, denouncing Israel for placing obstacles in the way
to establish peace, defending the rights of the Palestinian people
and urging the AL and the U.N. Security Council to confront
obstacles placed by Israel.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, Egyptian opposition parties have
called for holding an emergent Arab summit to tackle challenges
and hazards besetting the Arab world in light of Israel's
construction of the Jewish settlement in East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The parties, at a meeting Tuesday, also called for holding a
rally this week to denounce the Israeli settlement policy.
</P>
<P>
They also called for expelling the Israeli ambassador here
and withdrawing the Egyptian ambassador form Tel Aviv.
</P>
<P>
Arabs are infuriated by the Israeli housing project for Jews,
which they said caused a breakdown of Palestinian-Israeli
relations.
</P>
<P>
The past six days have witnessed widespread clashes between
Palestinian stone-throwers and Israeli soldiers in the West Bank
and a fatal suicide bomb attack in a Tel Aviv cafe last Friday, in
which three women were killed and 40 others wounded.
</P>
<P>
Egypt, together with the Palestinian National Authority and
Saudi Arabia, has drafted a plan that calls upon Arab and Islamic
countries to immediately freeze their relations with Israel and
suspend the Middle East multilateral cooperation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
