<HEADLINE> Chernomyrdin Holds Talks With Qian Qichen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 6 (Xinhua) -- Russian Prime Minister Viktor
Chernomyrdin met with Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign Minister
Qian Qichen here this afternoon and the talks between the two
sides were held in a friendly atmosphere.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, Chernomyrdin expressed satisfaction with
their talks and said that the talks conducted separately by
Russian President Boris Yeltsin and Foreign Minister Evgey
Primakov with Qian Qichen were fruitful.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Russia gives priority to development of the
relations of good-neighborliness, friendship and cooperation with
China in the Russian foreign policy.
</P>
<P>
The premier believed that the forthcoming visit of Chinese
President Jiang Zemin to Moscow will further promote the
relationship between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Qian Qichen conveyed the greetings and a
letter from Chinese Premier Li Peng to Chernomyrdin. The Russian
prime minister expressed thanks for it and asked Qian to pass on
his best wishes to Premier Li Peng.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin said that the Russian side is actively working for
the second regular meeting with Chinese Premier Li Peng, scheduled
for the second half of May.
</P>
<P>
Qian Qichen said that the mechanism of regular meeting between
the Chinese and Russian premiers has been put into practice since
Chinese Premier Li Peng paid a visit to Moscow at the end of last
year. It has brought many good results to development of the
relations between the two countries, he added.
</P>
<P>
Facts have proved, Qian said, the mechanism of regular meeting
at high level is very effective. It has important significance in
cooperation between the two countries in all fields, especially in
the fields of economy and trade, he said.
</P>
<P>
Qian Qichen believed that the upcoming second regular meeting
between the premiers of the two countries will also be
successful.
</P>
<P>
Both leaders put forward the great common goal of raising the
amount of the bilateral trade volume to 20 billion U.S. dollars by
the end of this century. Qian said that it is not hard to bring
about if only the two countries make common efforts.
</P>
<P>
China intends to find out new ways of cooperation with Russia
and to extend the cooperation, Qian said.
</P>
<P>
"We encourage those companies and enterprises, which have
strength and prestige, to make straight contacts with us," Qian
Qichen noted and hoped the departments concerned of the two sides
will begin studying upon it.
</P>
<P>
Sharing this opinion of Qian Qichen, Chernomyrdin said Russia
and China must create a long-term relationship of stable trade
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said that Russia wants to take part in building large
Chinese projects and will actively cooperate with China in the
fields of oil, natural gas, nuclear energy, machinery and
shipping.
</P>
<P>
The Russian side maintained that the two countries should help
supply each other's needs and gradually raise the trade volume,
Chernomyrdin said. At the same time, he said, the two governments
ought to actively open up their cooperation between some
industrial cities in the border areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
