<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Understands Russia's Worry About NATO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 26 (Xinhua) -- China completely understands
Russia's worry about the eastward expansion plans of the North
Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) and hopes to see the
improvement of Russia-U.S. relations, press spokesman of the
Foreign Ministry of China Shen Guofang said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Shen Guofang, who is accompanying Chinese Vice Prime Minister
and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen on his visit to Moscow, made the
remarks when replying to a question about China's attitude toward
the just finished Helsinki summit.
</P>
<P>
At a briefing, Shen Guofang told reporters that the development
of NATO should conform with the interests of other countries,
including Russia.
</P>
<P>
He said that China welcomes the consultations between Russia
and the United States on the NATO enlargement issue and is glad to
see the improvement of relations between them.
</P>
<P>
When asked if there is a concrete accord signed by Russia and
China on the Three Gorges project, Shen told reporters, "We
welcome the participation of Russia in the great project. Some of
the items are being considered and discussed between the Chinese
and Russian sides."
</P>
<P>
He said there is keen competition on the Three Gorges project,
and "I thought the Russian side was imbued with strong competition
since it has a solid foundation of warter and electric power."
</P>
<P>
In reply to the question on China-U.S. relations, Shen Guofang
said that relations between China and the U.S. are experiencing
trust, development and rubs.
</P>
<P>
Both China and the U.S. are great countries, Shen noted. "We
hope to keep the stable relations with the U.S. A good
relationship between the two countries would benefit world peace."
</P>
<P>
He stressed, "China will not make any concessions to the
problems concerning sovereign rights, independence and national
dignity." 
</P>
</TEXT>
