<HEADLINE> Arafat to Meet U.S. Envoy Dennis Ross in Rabat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RABAT, March 26 (Xinhua) -- The president of the Palestinian
autonomous authority Yasser Arafat will meet with the U.S.
presidential envoy for the Middle East Dennis Ross in Rabat on
Thursday on the current crisis of relations between Israel and
Palestine.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. embassy here said today in a communique that Ross was
sent by President Bill Clinton to meet Arafat and make an
evaluation of the situation, before making a report to U.S.
Secretary of State Madeleine Albright this weekend.
</P>
<P>
Arafat has agreed to have the meeting with Ross in a telephone
conversation with Madame Albright, said the communique.
</P>
<P>
Ross will go on to Israel to meet Prime Minister Benjamin
Netanyahu on Friday, the Moroccan news agency MAP quoted a U.S.
State Department official as saying.
</P>
<P>
Arafat has cut short his visit in Bangladesh and left Dacca
today.
</P>
<P>
The Al-Qods (Jerusalem) Committee of the Organization of
Islamic Conference will begin its 16th session Thursday in Rabat
to discuss the dangers posed against the holy city as Israel
persists on expanding its settlement in the Arab part of the city.
</P>
</TEXT>
