<HEADLINE> Detained Students of Addis Ababa University </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA. March 26 (Xinhua) -- The Addis Ababa Regional
Administration today announced it has accepted a statement of
apology by some of the Addis Ababa university students who were
recently detained for an illegal demonstration they staged.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued here, the administration said the
students' demand for an apology was accepted after they had
admitted their wrong in participating in the illegal rally.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Addis Ababa police commission said it has
released the students whom it said were put under custody for
illegal demonstration.
</P>
<P>
It was recalled that close to 200 university students were
detained last Friday for taking part in an illegal demonstration
here. 
</P>
</TEXT>
