<DOCNO> XIE19970327.0069 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-26 20:38 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> GCC States Welcome Iran's Initiative to Promote </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, March 26 (Xinhua) -- The Gulf Cooperation
Council (GCC) states today welcomed Iran's recent initiative
aimed at boosting relations with its six neighbors in the
region, Kuwait News Agency (KUNA) reported from Riyadh.
</P>
<P>
This was expressed by GCC foreign ministers in their final
statement after their 62nd meeting ending this afternoon in
the Saudi capital of Riyadh.
</P>
<P>
The statement said "the council welcomes Iran's new
initiative, which was made public by Iranian Foreign Minister
Ali Akbar Velayati during his last week's tour in the region."
</P>
<P>
The GCC members also welcomed the Iranian assurances given in
various contacts with the states of the region and expressed
readiness to react positively.
</P>
<P>
The GCC was ready to react positively to these initiatives and
help build trust with Iran, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
They considered the assurances made by velayati during his
recent tour and the meeting between Saudi Crown Prince Abdallah
ibn Abdul-Aziz and Iranian President Hashemi Rafsanjani on the
sidelines of the just-concluded summit of the Organization of the
Islamic Conference in Islamabad, Pakistan, were indications of
Iran's willingness to improve ties with the Gulf Arab countries,
according to the statement.
</P>
<P>
The GCC document added the ministers reviewed relations with
Iran based on the common will to promote them on the basis of
mutual respect and non-interference in each other's internal
affairs.
</P>
<P>
It also underlined the need to reject to resort to force and
called for solving differences through peaceful means and in
accordance with the international law.
</P>
<P>
The ministers also reiterated the United Arab Emirates' (UAE)
sovereignty over the islands of Abu Moussa and Greater and
Lesser Tunbs in the Gulf which are currently held by Iran.
</P>
<P>
They also reaffirmed their support to all peaceful measures by
the UAE in restoring its sovereignty over the islands.
</P>
<P>
The islands issue is a key problem blocking the normalization
of relations between Iran and the GCC which groups Saudi Arabia,
the UAE, Kuwait, Oman, Qatar and Bahrain, besides differences in
the U.S. military existence in the Gulf region and others areas.
</P>
</TEXT>
