<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves 89 Million Dollar Loan for Algeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, March 26 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank Tuesday approved
in Washington an 89 million U.S. dollar loan for Algeria to help
its land management projects, especially in the northwest of the
country, reported the Algerian press service APS.
</P>
<P>
The loan is refundable in 17 years with a standard interest
rate of the bank and a five-year period of repayment.
</P>
<P>
The Algerian government is launching a campaign to prevent
erosion of soil, to plant trees, and consolidate facilities for
controlling flood, the cost which are estimated at 126.06 million
U.S. dollars, said APS.
</P>
<P>
The government is also planning to train more women living in
villages in such trade as craft industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
