<HEADLINE> Egyptian Students Protest Against Israeli Settlement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of students of Egypt's
Alexandria University today staged a demonstration in protest
against the Israeli building of a new Jewish neighborhood in Arab
East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The students, carrying banners denouncing Israeli repressive
practices in the occupied Arab lands and Prime Minister Binyamin
Netanyahu's settlement policy, urged their government to stand up
to Israel.
</P>
<P>
It is the latest of a string of protests in Egypt against the
Jabal Abu Ghoneim or Har Homa project and Israeli attempts to
Judaize Jerusalem, which is holy to Christians, Muslims and Jews
alike.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, about 50 women from the Egyptian
trade unions and political parties today gathered outside the
headquarters of the Arab League (AL) here to protest against
Israel's settlement activities.
</P>
<P>
The demonstrators held banners and shouted slogans such as
"Jerusalem is Arab," demanding an emergency Arab summit to
discuss Israel's settlement policies in Arab lands.
</P>
<P>
Cairo University students held a two-day demonstration on
campus since Monday, denouncing Israel for placing obstacles in
the way to establish peace, defending the rights of the
Palestinian people and urging the AL and the United Nations
Security Council to confront obstacles placed by Israel.
</P>
<P>
Egypt, together with the Palestinian National Authority and
Saudi Arabia, has drafted a plan that calls upon Arab and Islamic
countries to immediately freeze their relations with Israel and
suspend the Middle East multilateral cooperation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
