<HEADLINE> Algerian Security Force Kills Chief Terrorist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Algeria's security forces killed
Tuesday afternoon three Islamic militants, including a chief of
the militant group Islamic Front of Armed Defense (FIDA), said
security forces in a communique today.
</P>
<P>
Seddoudi Abdelkader, Alias Ahmed Abu Al Fida or Abdallah, who
was considered to be one of the most dangerous terrorists in the
country, was killed with two of his collaborators in the commune
of Bab Al Oued in Algiers.
</P>
<P>
Abdelkader was held responsible for a number of terrorist
attacks in the capital Algiers.
</P>
<P>
The Algerian security forces have been intensifying sweeping
operations against the country's Islamic militants, in preparation
for the legislative elections scheduled for June 5. 
</P>
</TEXT>
