<HEADLINE> U.S. Expels Belarus Diplomat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 26 (Xinhua) -- The United States today
ordered the expulsion of a Belarus diplomat in retaliation for
similar action against an American envoy in Minsk.
</P>
<P>
First Secretary and consul Vladimir Gramyka at the Belarus
Embassy in Washington was given 24 hours to leave the United
States, State Department spokesman John Dinger said.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, Belarus police detained Serge Alexandrov, first
secretary at the U.S. Embassy in Minsk, during an anti-government
march. The Belarus government ordered Alexandrov home after
accusing him of being a CIA agent who helped organize the rally.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, the U.S. government announced that U.S. Ambassador
Kenneth Yalowitz was being recalled for consultations to discuss
the rapid deterioration in relations between the two countries.
</P>
