<DOCNO> XIE19970327.0081 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Signed Article On Dalai's Visit to Taiwan (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The article noted that the relations between the Dalai and
Taiwan authorities have been inconsistent in the past few
years. Although late Chiang Kai-shek and Chiang Ching-kuo had
attempted to use the Dalai against the Communist Party of China
when they were in power, they insisted that Tibet is part of
China. Therefore, it was impossible for them to sit in the same
"boat" and the Dalai failed to land on the island.
</P>
<P>
But things have changed, the article said. Those who are in
power in the Taiwan authorities are gradually collaborating with
"Taiwan Independence" forces. To split China, the two sides
decided to reinforce the collaboration.
</P>
<P>
The Dalai's visit is against the background of the increasingly
rampant splittism on the island, the article stressed, it is safe
to say that the Taiwan authorities have taken an extremely
dangerous step on the road of separating the country, and the
splittist forces on the island have already collaborated with the
"Tibet Independence" forces.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Government has issued several serious warnings
about Taiwan authorities' invitation of the Dalai to visit Taiwan,
expressing the hope that Taiwan authorities would adopt prudent
and wise attitude and avoid any acts that might infringe upon the
unification and unity of the country. But the Taiwan Authorities
kept going their own way and pulling the wool over the eyes of
Taiwan people.
</P>
<P>
It is the common aspiration of all the Chinese people to adhere
to the principle of "One China", fight against splittism and
safeguard national unification and unity, the article said. It is
an irreversible historical tide. Any attempt to split the country,
either "Taiwan Independence" or "Tibet Independence", will be
doomed to failure. 
</P>
</TEXT>
