<HEADLINE> Israeli FM: Violence Will Destroy Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Foreign Minister
David Levy said today that violence and terror would destroy the
Middle East peace process, Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with Migueio Angel Moratinos, European Union
special envoy to the Middle East, Levy accused the Palestinian
National Authority (PNA) of using the masses and Arab states to
isolate Israel.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli foreign minister said the issue of Har Homa, also
known as Jabal Abu Ghoneim, a controversial area under
construction of news homes for Jews on the southeastern outskirts
of Jerusalem, was being used as an excuse.
</P>
<P>
Levy added that the problem is not just the current crisis
between Israel and the PNA, due to the Har Homa building, but
rather a threat of terror and violence.
</P>
<P>
He said that even if the crisis was resolved, Israel would
not agree to extremist activities being used as a tool by the
PNA.
</P>
<P>
Moratinos promised he would speak to Esmat Abdul Meguid,
secretary-general of the Arab League, in an attempt to moderate
Arab expressions against Israel, and to improve the atmosphere in
the region.
</P>
<P>
Moratinos, who is also Spanish ambassador to Israel, said
that he would convey the Israeli concerns to PNA President
Yasser Arafat during their scheduled meeting Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
