CAIRO -- Egyptian Foreign Ministers Amr Moussa and his Syrian
counterpart Farouq al-Shara Thursday held Israel responsible for
the grave crisis facing the Mideast peace process.
</P>
<P>
In a telephone interview with Egyptian Voice of Arab radio this
morning, the two ministers said that Israel's settlement project
in East Jerusalem contradicts with the international law and
relevant U.N. resolutions.
</P>
<P>
SEOUL -- South Korean prosecutors said Thursday that they have
found massive hidden assets of the bankrupt Hanbo business group
and they were going to arrest the chairman of Hanbo group.
</P>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG -- The South African National Defense Forces
(SANDF)'s territorial headquarters, groups and part-time forces
would be restructured and streamlined to improve their efficiency,
local daily Business Day reported Thursday.
</P>
