<HEADLINE> Shanghai Celebrate Big-score Victory in Soccer League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Last season's runnerr-up Shanghai
Shenhua hammered Guangdong Hongyuan 4-1 in their away-match at the
Chinese Football League in Guangzhou on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The visiting squad showed all-around superiorities throughout
the game.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai opened the scorings in the 18th minute through French
player Perez on a throw-in. The Frenchmen found the net with a
shock left-foot goal after laying down on the ground.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai eleven gave the home fans another heavy blow when
striker Xie Hui headed home in the 61st minute on a corner-kick
from his teammate Shen Si, making it 2-0.
</P>
<P>
The match turned to somewhat ill-tempered in the mid of the
second half as the home team conceded two goals in a span of four
minutes, both by penalties.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong goal-keeper Ou chuliang, also the Chinese national
squad keeper, offered a penalty chance to his opponents in the
32nd minute after he brought down a forward of Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Substitute Qi Hong gained the second penalty for Shanghai after
making a solo charge into the area.
</P>
<P>
Fan Zhiyi, captain of the visiting team, converted the two
penalties.
</P>
<P>
The host team finally got something consolation as Li Yuzhan
scored the only goal on a rebound of a freekick, just two minutes
before the final whistle.
</P>
<P>
"Anyway, my players had tried their best, " said Guo Yijun,
head coach of the Guangdong team, "obviously, the Shanghai team
are stronger than us. They gave us much pressure, leaving us
little chance to enter their area."
</P>
<P>
The coach said that the loose defense was another reason for
their failure. But he added that the loss would not affect their
next league tie against Yanbian Aodong.
</P>
<P>
Dalian Wanda extended their unbeaten record to 37 matches after
outplaying Tianjin Lifei 2-0 in their away-match to collect three
straight wins after three rounds this season.
</P>
<P>
Teenager Wang Peng opened the scorings in the 17th minute while
Zhang Enhua, defender of the Chinese national team, added
the second with a volley.
</P>
<P>
In the other matches of the day, Qingdao Hainiu defeated
Vanguards Huandao 2-0. Hainiu shared the second place alongside
with Shanghai Shenhua; Beijing Guo'an beat Jinan Taishan 2-1,
Sichuan Quanxing beat Yanbian Aodong 3-1 and August First drew
with Guangzhou Apollo 0-0. 
</P>
</TEXT>
