<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Unemployment Rate Declines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Unemployment rate between December
1996 and February 1997 dropped to 3.4 percent in Macao, latest
statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics Department
show that the jobless rate went down 0.4 percent from the period
between November 1996 and January 1997.
</P>
<P>
The jobless rate hit the highest of 4.6 percent last year.
</P>
<P>
The figures collected from a survey among 3,600 households also
show that half-unemployment rate rose by 0.1 percent to 0.6
percent in the December 1996--February 1997 period.
</P>
<P>
Half of the residents surveyed at the time were of working age,
which is above 14 years old, down 0.3 percentage points from the
period of November 1996 to January 1997.
</P>
<P>
The government said last week that it plans to resume the
import of migrant labor force for some industries like textile and
garment-making, lifting a 19-month ban soon.
</P>
<P>
Economic officials said that Macao's economy is seeing a
revival following a two-year slowdown.  
</P>
</TEXT>
