<HEADLINE> UEFA Imposes Life Ban On Former Swiss Referee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, March 27 (Xinhua) -- UEFA imposed a life ban Thursday
on former Swiss referee Kurt Roethlisberger for attempted bribery.
</P>
<P>
Roethlisberger admitted attempted bribery during investigations
into a European Champions' League match between Grasshopper Zurich
and Auxerre on October 30.
</P>
<P>
UEFA said Roethlisberger had contacted Grasshopper general
manager Erich Vogel and visited his office 12 days before the tie.
</P>
<P>
The former umpire hinted to the manager that he was friendly
with the match's referee Vadim Zhuk of Belarus and it would be
easy to arrange the matter. Roethlisberger's actions were
reported to UEFA by Grasshopper.
</P>
<P>
UEFA said investigations to the Belarussian were still
continuing. Zhuk will not officiate as a FIFA referee until the
investigations have been concluded.
</P>
<P>
Grasshopper beat Auxerre 3-1 in that match. 
</P>
</TEXT>
