<HEADLINE> More Overseas Investment Introduced in Henan's Grain Processing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENZHOU, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Henan Province
drew close to 9.26 million US dollars of overseas investment for
local grain-processing development in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The funds was used in projects in non-staple food processing,
timber-processing, meat-processing, and soft drinks industry.
</P>
<P>
A total of some 1.2 billion US dollars of investment flowed
into the province last year, up 17.2 percent over 1995. The money
is expected to speed up local agriculture and energy development,
and transportation industry. 
</P>
