<HEADLINE> Signed Article Condemns Dalai's Trip to Taiwan (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 27 (Xinhua) -- The Xinhua News Agency today
published a signed article that denounced Dalai Lama's visit to
Taiwan, which started on 22 this month.
</P>
<P>
The article, written by Gang Jun and titled "A Farce of
Splitting the Country", said that the so-called "religious visit"
to Taiwan by the Dalai Lama is in fact a joint attempt to split
China by elements of "Taiwan independence" and "Tibet
independence."
</P>
<P>
"It is common public opinion that this trip of Dalai harbors
evil intentions," it noted.
</P>
<P>
It pointed out that the invitation for the Dalai Lama sent from
some people headed by the "Chinese Buddhist Association" in Taiwan
merely served as a cover.
</P>
<P>
"The Taiwan authorities were not only involved in this event
from the very beginning, but the actual directors behind the
scene," it said.
</P>
<P>
According to reports of some Taiwan newspapers, it said, Lee
Teng-hui has been a long-time "admirer" of the Dalai Lama, and the
two have had correspondence for a long period of time.
</P>
<P>
Taiwan officials openly admitted that Dalai's trip to the
island resulted from the "instructions of top authorities," and
demanded that "the work of publicity avoid politics and be
absolutely confined to the field of religion."
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the article added, the "Chinese Buddhist Association"
inf Taiwan, which was in charge of the invitation, also made
remarks that "the work of the authorities is behind the curtain
and should not be leaked to outsiders."
</P>
<P>
"Thus it can be seen that the farce has been staged with the
meticulous planning and full support of the Taiwan authorities
headed by Lee Teng-hui," it said.
</P>
<P>
It said that although the Taiwan authorities have repeatedly
claimed that the trip of Dalai to Taiwan is purely religious and
non-governmental, it is simply not the truth.
</P>
