<HEADLINE> Zhejiang to Produce 380,000 Tons Iodized Table Salt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, March 27 (Xinhua) -- East China's coastal Zhejiang
Province has begun a project to produce 380,000 tons of iodized
table salt this year.
</P>
<P>
The salt will be mainly produced in the local coastal areas in
Daishan, Ningbo, Xiangshan, and Sanmen.
</P>
<P>
The project is expected to help the province put an end to a
disease which is caused by shortage of iodine by the turn of the
century.
</P>
<P>
In order to conduct the project, Zhejiang has received the
first phase of loans from the China State Development Bank,
totalling 5.72 million yuan, and 800,000 yuan of state funds for
development of table salt with iodine.  
</P>
