<HEADLINE> Signed Article (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 27 (Xinhua) -- The Taiwan authorities first
wanted to adopt a low-key profile to the Dalai's visit to Taiwan,
saying that Lee Tung Hui would not meet the Dalai Lama.
</P>
<P>
However, with the day of the Dalai's visit approaching, the
real aspect of the thing revealed itself gradually. In fact, Lee
Tung Hui has always had his own opinion on the event, saying: "The
meeting (between me and Dalai Lama) will certainly take place,"
and the questions only lie "in which capacity, and on what
occasion."
</P>
<P>
Then the Dalai Lama expressed his wish several days ago to meet
with Lee in whatever conditions, which provides Lee with a rare
opportunity he will not miss to present a performance.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile the "Legislate Yuan" has also adopted a resolution to
welcome the Dalai Lama to deliver a speech, and the Democratic
Progressive Party has spared no efforts to require cities and
counties under their leadership to hoist the "snow mountain and
lion" flag, some activists for "Taiwan independence" even openly
require the Taiwan authorities to recognize "the independence of
Tibet" through the visit of Dalai Lama.
</P>
<P>
Most opinions in Taiwan pointed out that "as an advocator of
Tibet independence, the Dalai Lama's visit is unable to cover its
strong political colors, even though it is defined as a visit to
spread religious doctrines."
</P>
<P>
In fact, the political implication of the Dalai Lama's visit to
Taiwan is too apparent to hide, but the Taiwan authorities
absurdly called it "a religious and nongovernmental one". Such
awkward handling obviously reveals the true untold intentions
harbored by the Taiwan authorities to invite the Dalai Lama to
Taiwan.
</P>
