<HEADLINE> US Ford Motors to Hold More Shares in China Auto Venture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Sources from Ford Motors (China)
Ltd. today announced it will increase its shares in Jiangling
Motors Co., a key local light vehicle producer.
</P>
<P>
Ford will increase its equity of Jiangling from the current 20
percent to approximately 30 percent as part of Jiangling's B-share
offering.
</P>
<P>
B shares are traded by overseas investors in the Chinese
bourses.
</P>
<P>
Jiangling is to float 170 million B shares, of which Ford will
purchase about 120 million shares with a total stock value of 54.5
million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The agreement still awaits formal approval by Jiangling's
Shareholders' Board and Chinese government agencies.
</P>
<P>
Ford purchased 20 percent of Jiangling's shares with 40 million
dollars in August, 1995.
</P>
<P>
According to sources, the investment is to go to the joint
development and manufacture of a new light commercial vehicle
based on Jingling's powertrain and the production technology of
Transit, a van produced by Ford in Europe. The six-seat and
12-seat models are expected to come out by the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
To minimize the cost, the two sides agreed to use the existing
Jiangling and Ford facilities in China, including the five auto
parts and components joint ventures already clinched by Ford in
China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
