<HEADLINE> Chinese Official Meets Portuguese Defense Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Chen Ziying, deputy director of
the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office under the State Council,
met here today with Portuguese Defense Minister Antonio Vitorino.
</P>
<P>
Extending welcome to the minister, Chen said the Chinese
government has attached great importance to Sino-Portugese
friendly relations and that he believes the minister's visit would
further promote the growth of bilateral friendly and cooperative
ties.
</P>
<P>
China and Portugal have maintained a sound cooperation since
the signing of the Joint Declaration on the Macao issue 10 years
ago.
</P>
<P>
Through the work of the Sino-Portuguese Joint Liaison Group in
the past years, both sides has made progress on settling some
issues in Macao's transitional period, he added.
</P>
<P>
As the return of Macao in 1999 is approaching, there is still
much work left for the two sides, he acknowledged.
</P>
<P>
He said leaders of China and Portugal all advocated to settle
issues with a far-sighted attitude, and that this is helpful to
maintain Macao's stable transition, smooth transfer of power, as
well as to its long-term prosperity and stability, and in the
basic interests of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
With the guarantee of Deng Xiaoping's great concept of "one
country, two systems" as well as the friendly cooperation between
China and Portugal, any problem can be resolved, as long as the
two sides continue to have consultations on the basis of the Joint
Declaration, Chen said.
</P>
<P>
Vitorino expressed his agreement to Chen's view, and said that
the Portuguese government is very clear about the Chinese
government's confidence in Macao's future development, and they
are also confident with it. 
</P>
