<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Australian Prime
Minister John Howard said here today that both Australia and
Singapore support China's entry into the World Trade Organization
(WTO).
</P>
<P>
Howard, who was here on a three-day official visit, said this
after signing a new air services pact with his Singaporean
counterpart Goh Chok Tong.
</P>
