<HEADLINE> Share Prices Fall on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Share prices declined on the
Singapore market after surging for three days with the benchmark
Straits Times Industrials Index falling by 12.68 points to close
at 2098.92 points today.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume was thin at 177.44 million units, worth
357.75 million Singapore dollars (about 251.94 million US
dollars). Declines overwhelmed advances by 263 to 70, while 276
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
MBF Land was the most actively traded stock as it registered a
turnover of 9.12 million units. It was followed by MBF Holdings
which had 6.86 million shares traded. Tongkah Warrant 99 was next
with 5.49 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Van Der Hurst Warrant 98 led the gainers of the day as it rose
by 76 cents to finish at 4.7 dollars. South Bank Foreign A gained
22 cents to close at 4.22 Singapore dollars, while the Thai Prime
Fund picked up by 20 cents to end at 10.8 dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 was the biggest loser as it fell
by one Singapore dollar to close at 13.4 Singapore dollars. Asia
Pacific declined by 85 cents to end at 7.15 dollars, while GE Life
and the Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign lost 50 cents each
to finish at 20.9 and 26.1 dollars respectively.  
</P>
