<HEADLINE> Activities Aimed at Splitting the Motherland Will be in Vain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Any activities aimed at splitting
the motherland and undermining national unity will be in vain,
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Cui Tiankai said here today.
</P>
<P>
When asked to comment on today's meeting between the Dalai Lama
and Lee Teng-hui, Cui said that realizing the motherland's
reunification is the common desire of the entire Chinese people,
anyone who goes against the historical trend will be doomed in
failure.
</P>
<P>
Cui noted that the Dalai Lama has engaged in activities aimed
at splitting the motherland for a long time, adding that the Dalai
Lama went to Taiwan obviously with political intent.
</P>
<P>
"Taiwan and Tibet are two inalienable parts of China," he said,
"We are opposed to anyone's activities of splitting the motherland
and undermining national unity in any place, in any form."
</P>
<P>
</P>
