<HEADLINE> NPC Vice-Chairwoman Accepts Bolivian National Medal of Honor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Chen Muhua, vice-chairwoman of
the Standing Committee of the Chinese National People's Congress,
was conferred the Bolivian national medal of honor here today for
her outstanding efforts in safeguarding the rights of Chinese
women.
</P>
<P>
Mrs. Ximena De Sanchez, accompanying President Sanchez on his
current China tour, awarded Chen the honorary "Andes Condor" medal
on behalf of the Bolivian government at the Great Hall of the
People.
</P>
<P>
Highly appreciating Chen's successful organization of the
Fourth World Women's Conference held in Beijing in 1995 and her
contributions to safeguarding Chinese women's rights, Ximena said
Chen is well worthy of the honor.
</P>
<P>
Chen, also president of the All-China Women's Federation, noted
that the medal represents not only the development of
Sino-Bolivian relations, but also the deep friendship between the
women of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
She hoped that the two countries would exert concerted efforts
to contribute more to their friendship and the cause of seeking
world equality, development, peace, and progress.
</P>
<P>
The medal of "Andes Condor", established in 1925, honors those
who have made prominent contributions to Bolivia. 
