<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Basic Law Guarantees Smooth Handover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, March 27 (Xinhua) -- A smooth handover of power in Macao
will be achieved as the Basic Law of Macao, which legalizes the
policy of "one country, two systems," is becoming known to more
and more people in the territory, a senior Chinese official based
here said.
</P>
<P>
Wang Qiren, director of the Xinhua News Agency Macao Branch,
said at a gathering Wednesday night to mark the 4th anniversary of
promulgation of on the Basic Law that the law has boosted Macao
residents' confidence in their future.
</P>
<P>
"The policy of 'one country, two systems' in the realization of
a peaceful reunification of the motherland is a great creation of
Deng Xiaoping," he said. "And the Basic Law has put that policy in
the form of law so that it can be implemented."
</P>
<P>
Promulgated on March 31, 1993, the Basic Law stipulates that
the capitalist system and the basic style of life in Macao will
remain unchanged for 50 years after the handover. Macao will also
enjoy a high degree of autonomy.
</P>
<P>
Wang said the law has set the orientation for major
transitional affairs, and is the source of confidence for all
Macao residents.
</P>
<P>
In addition, he said that Hong Kong's return to China and the
convening of the 15th national congress of the Communist Party of
China (CPC) later this year will both have a positive effect on a
smooth handover and a stable transition.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong's return to the motherland will offer valuable
experience and encourage Macao residents to take an active part in
handling the transitional affairs," Wang said. "The 15th Party
congress will push forward China's reform and opening to the
outside world, and a stronger motherland is the best guarantee for
Macao's stability and development."
</P>
<P>
The director praised the Macao Basic Law Promotion Association
for its achievements in promoting the law, and pledged further
support for the association.
</P>
<P>
The association has launched a promotion campaign among local
residents. A special TV program it co-produced with China Central
Television Station (CCTV) on Macao and the basic law will be
broadcast as of March 30 on several channels of CCTV.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
