<HEADLINE> Ready to Negotiate, But Never Share Power Share: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOME, March 27 (Xinhua) -- The Zairean rebels' team attending
the special summit of the Organization African Union (OAU) on the
Zaire conflict said here today that they are ready to negotiate
but will never share power with President Mobutu Sese Seko.
</P>
<P>
The two-member delegation mandated by rebel leader Laurent
Kabila arrived here on Tuesday for the first extraordinary OAU
summit aimed at finding a peaceful solution to the Zaire crisis.
</P>
<P>
The two rebel delegates, Bizima Kahaha and Gaetan Kakudji,
told reporters at a news conference that "we are ready to hold
negotiations in any country as long as they are serious".
</P>
<P>
They added they "are very excited to have learned for the first
time that people in Kinshasa agree to start to negotiate in a few
days to come."
</P>
<P>
Kahaha noted that they have been asking for negotiations for
more than five months without receiving any answer from the
government, adding that only a few days ago did they learn the
government is "going to be serious".
</P>
<P>
The rebel delegates said that they do not "trust them too
much".
</P>
<P>
Asked if they are going to share power with President Mobutu
as indicated by his ruling Movement of Popular Revolution on
Tuesday, Kahaha said: "Never."
</P>
<P>
They stated that they are here not for negotiations, noting
the government delegation for the meeting is not mandated by
President Mobutu to negotiate.
</P>
<P>
They said they will have a team to negotiate only with
President Mobutu's fully-mandated delegation. enditem

