<HEADLINE> Thai Tourism Sector Urged to Focus on Local Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, March 27 (Xinhua) -- The Thai tourism business is
expected to shift its focus to local tourists as the Tourism
Authority of Thailand (TAT) is seeking new strategies to develop
the country's tourism industry.
</P>
<P>
The change is urged in a tourism development master plan
prepared by the Thailand development research institute for the
TAT.
</P>
<P>
The focus of attention should be given to local tourists
instead of foreign tourists, according to the plan revealed by the
TAT today.
</P>
<P>
The initiative is intended to encourage local officials to take
serious actions to improve the infrastructure and service
facilities to cater to tourism, while helping upgrade the
standards of living of Thais.
</P>
<P>
Once improvements are made, they will be equally applicable to
foreign tourists, the plan said.
</P>
<P>
The plan also proposed short-term and long-term goals for Thai
tourism development.
</P>
<P>
The immediate aim between 1998-2003 is to focus on development
which will preserve the country's culture and environment with the
ultimate goal of turning Thailand into a world class tourism
destination, according to the plan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
