<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Four Tested Positive in Asian Cup Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Asian Football Confederation
(AFC) confirmed for the first time Thursday that four players
failed tests at Asian Cup last December.
</P>
<P>
The players have not been identified, but the failures were
after the semi-finals and the final of Asia's top soccer event.
</P>
<P>
AFC general secretary Peter Velappan ended months of
speculation since the tournament by saying the failures were
"deeply disappointing".
</P>
<P>
AFC sources said the cases had now been referred to the
International Football Federation (FIFA) to decide what action to
take.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia, United Arab Emirates, Kuwait and Iran reached the
semi-finals. Saudi Arabia beat UAE in the final.
</P>
<P>
The only previous drug failure at an Asian tournament was
Thailand's Srisak Kidalee at the 1994 Asian Games in Hiroshima,
Japan. He was banned for a year and the Football Association of
Thailand was fined 3,000 U.S. dollars. 
</P>
