<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Raises Prices of Petroleum Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia's Ministry of Trade
and Industry has issued a statement under which the petroleum
price was raised from 2.33 Birr to 2.64 Birr (0.4 U.S. Dollar) a
liter from today.
</P>
<P>
According to the new price adjustment which takes effect as
from today, the price of butane gas went up from 3.34 Birr to
3.69 Birr per kilogram.
</P>
<P>
Other petroleum products are also adjusted respectively.
</P>
<P>
One Dollar equals to 6.631 Birr in this country.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said the price adjustment is in accordance with
the decisions of the council of ministers on price regulation
every six months with an aim to have the prices parallel with the
world market.
</P>
<P>
As an oil-imported country, Ethiopia had to use 235 million
Dollars to import oil and petroleum products in 1995/96.
</P>
<P>
The last price adjustment of petroleum products was in
September 1996 when the petroleum price increased from 2.00 Birr
to 2.33 Birr a liter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
