<HEADLINE> S. Leone not Seeks Extradiction for Sankoh Held </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
in Nigeria
</P>
<P>
FREETOWN, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Sierra Leone has not asked
Nigeria to extradict Sierra Leone's deposed rebel leader Foday
Sankoh#,Attorney General Solomon Berewa Rsaid said in an
interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
"The Sierra Leone government has not considered the
extradiction option as yet," Berewa said.
</P>
<P>
He declined to say whether such request will be made in the
future.
</P>
<P>
Despite recent calls from legal institutions in the country
for Sankoh's trial on war crimes, "we are not doing anything
about Sankoh now," a spokesman for law officers said.
</P>
<P>
Sankoh was arrested at Lagos airport about two weeks ago
after a quantity of arms and ammunition were found on him. Now he
is still being questioned by Nigerian security officials.
</P>
<P>
Sankoh was deposed from the leadership by senior members of
the Revolutionary United Front (RUF) organization who accused him
of "intransigence toward the peace agreement" signed in Abidjan
last November.
</P>
<P>
Under the peace accord, Sankoh should be benefited from an
amnesty for crimes he had committed before November 30 but not
afterwards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
