<DOCNO> XIE19970327.0164 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CMC Vice-Chairman Meets Bahraini Military Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Chairman of China's Central
Military Commission (CMC) Chi Haotian met here this afternoon with
a military delegation from Bahrain headed by Rashid Al-Khalifa,
assistant chief of Staff of Bahrain's Defense Force.
</P>
<P>
This is the first military delegation of Bahrain ever to visit
China since the two countries established diplomatic relations in
1989.
</P>
<P>
Extending a warm welcome, Chi, who is also State Councillor and
Defense Minister, said that although China and Bahrain only enjoy
a few years of diplomatic links, bilateral relations have
developed rapidly, and there is a good cooperative basis for the
two governments, the two peoples and the two armed forces.
</P>
<P>
He noted that both China and Bahrain pursue an independent
foreign policy of peace, and they are facing the same question of
peace and development.
</P>
<P>
The two countries also share many common points in
international affairs, and they both oppose hegemonism and power
politics, added Chi.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that China always holds that all countries,
big or small, rich or poor, strong or weak, are equal members of
the international community.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government attaches importance to Rashid's current
visit to China, believing that this visit will further push
forward the development of friendship and cooperation between the
two countries and the two armed forces.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Chi briefed the visitors on China's
domestic situation and its defensive national defense policy, and
he also criticized the concept of so-called "China threat".
</P>
<P>
Rashid said that China is an important force for safeguarding
world peace and stability, and his visit here is aimed at
furthering the friendship and cooperation between Bahrain and
China, as well as between their two armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Rashid also expressed his thanks for China's just stance on
supporting the third world countries and people at the UN General
Assembly.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Chief of the General Staff of the Chinese People's
Liberation Army Wu Quanxu and Bahraini Ambassador to China Hussein
Rashid Al-Sabbagh were present at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Bahraini delegation is here as guest of China's National
Defense Ministry.  
</P>
</TEXT>
