<HEADLINE> Photo Exhibition to Show Lives of Shanghai People in Australia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, together with an
Australian company, will hold a photo exhibition in May aimed at
boosting non-governmental exchanges between China and Australia.
</P>
<P>
The show, entitled "Shanghai People in Australia," will feature
some 350 photos illustrating the lives of people going from
Shanghai to Australia and their contributions to Sino-Australian
exchanges of culture, economy, science and technology.
</P>
<P>
Australian Premier John Howard praised the event as promoting
bilateral contacts of the two peoples in his congratulatory
message to the show's organizing committee.
</P>
<P>
The city sources said that another photo show, "Shanghai's
Yesterday, Today and Tomorrow" held last August in Melbourne, drew
great attention from both Chinese staying in Australia and
Australians,
</P>
<P>
China reportedly is the sixth biggest trade partner of
Australia, and more than half of the business between the two
sides have been via Shanghai, the most important port city in the
country.  
</P>
