<HEADLINE> Jiangsu Has Two Million Pagers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, March 27 (Xinhua) -- A contingent of 905,000 people
has joined the huge army of pager-owners in east China's Jiangsu
Province, bringing the total number to two million at the end of
1996.
</P>
<P>
This ranks Jiangsu the third in the country in terms of pager
owners, after Guangdong and Liaoning provinces.
</P>
<P>
The coastal province invested more than 100 million yuan in
1996 to revamp its paging networks, which now cover all cities,
counties and almost all townships.
</P>
<P>
Paging services have witnessed rapid growth in China over the
past several years, as the demand for modern telecommunications
becomes more acute.  
