<BODY>
<HEADLINE> CPC Delegation Arrives in Dhaka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, March 27 (Xinhua) -- A delegation of the Communist Party
of China (CPC) arrived here today on a week-long visit to
Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
Greeting the Chinese delegation at the airport, State Minister
for Foreign Affairs Abu Hasan Chowdhury, who is also the
International Secretary of Bangladesh's ruling Awami (people's)
League (AL), emphasized the importance of the relations between
the CPC and AL.
</P>
<P>
Chowdhury said the two parties have maintained official
relations since AL President Sheikh Hasina visited China in 1993.
"After taking office as prime minister in 1996, Sheikh Hasina
chose China as the country to pay her first official visit to," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Ma Qizhi, head of the delegation and a member of the CPC
Central Committee, said he hoped his visit would further
consolidate the relations between the two parties and the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
The delegation is scheduled to meet with Prime Minister Sheikh
Hasina next Tuesday and hold official talks on Sunday with Foreign
Minister Abdus Samad Azad, who is also chairman of the AL's
Foreign Relations Committee.  
</P>
