<HEADLINE> US Vice-President Visits Home of Terracotta Soldiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, March 27 (Xinhua) -- US Vice-President Al Gore arrived
in this capital city of northwest China's Shaanxi Province today
for a one-day visit to the site of world-renowned terracotta
soldiers.
</P>
<P>
Governor Cheng Andong of Shaanxi greeted and met with Gore at
the Terracotta Museum, and briefed the US vice president on the
history, culture and economic development of the province.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed his hope to increase economic cooperation
with the US.
</P>
<P>
Gore said he was happy to have the opportunity to visit Xi'an,
and praised the inland province's effort in developing the economy
and protecting the environment.
</P>
<P>
Afterwards, the US vice-president, his wife Tipper Gore and
entourage toured the two sites where the buried life-size figures
of warriors and horses were found in the 1970s.
</P>
<P>
Gore commented that the terracotta figures are a wonder of the
world and when signing the museum guest book , he thanked Chinese
archeologists for repairing and preserving the relics which
represent human civilization.
</P>
<P>
The US vice-president, his wife Tipper Gore and party were
greeted at the airport today by Shaanxi Vice-Governor Jiang
Xinzhen and Vice-Mayor Zhang Fan of Xi'an.
</P>
<P>
Accompanied by Chen Jinhua, chairman of the Chinese Government
Reception Committee and minister in charge of the State Planning
Commission, Gore and his party later proceeded to Shanghai, the
last stop of his first China trip. 
