<DOCNO> XIE19970327.0194 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambia's Tea Firm to Get Big Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Zambia's Kawambwa Tea Company
(KTC), located in Central Province and sold to Britain's Metal
Distributors recently, is to get three million U.S. Dollars to
boost production, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
This was revealed by Hemant Jalan, the director of KTC new
owner Metal Distributors (uk) in Ndola, the capital of Central
Province on Wednesday, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The KTC project situated in an inaccessible and remote area of
Central Province will need tremendous amount of inputs to bring
the entire estate back into full productivity in the next two
years.
</P>
<P>
Jalan said that the new move will create additional employment
for about 200 to 300 people.
</P>
<P>
KTC has recently been privatized by the Zambia Privatization
Agency and bought by Metal Distributors which is a part of the
Binani group.
</P>
<P>
The Binani group has already invested two million Dollars in a
copper rod project in the southern African country with an aim to
expand the production from 3,000 tons to 18,000 tons per annum.
</P>
