<HEADLINE> Kuwait Urges US to Stop Israel from Building Settlement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-four Kuwaiti members
of parliament (MP) signed a petition Wednesday asking
U.S. President Bill Clinton for his intervention to stop Israel
from building new Jewish settlement in Arab East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The MPs said in the letter, a copy of which obtained today,
that the U.S. veto of the U.N. Security Council resolution
demanding Israel to stop the settlement plan has "shocked and
pained them."
</P>
<P>
The veto represented "a green signal for Israel to go ahead in
the project and angered the feeling of over one billion Muslims
around the globe," it said.
</P>
<P>
The city of Jerusalem is linked to "our Islamic faith, Arab
culture and identity," they said.
</P>
<P>
Israel has started to build the widely criticized settlement in
East Jerusalem in defiance of the strong opposition of the
Palestinians and accusation from the world Islamic community.
</P>
<P>
"We hope, Mr. President, that you would intervene to stop the
construction of the Jewish settlement. We are aware that such a
provocation to our faith will return the whole region to tension
and anger," the letter said.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait had officially condemned the Israeli move and said it
jeopardized peace effort in the region.
</P>
<P>
In another development Wednesday, hundreds of Kuwaiti students
held a public rally to protest against the Jewish
settlement, during which two Israeli flags were burnt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
