<DOCNO> XIE19970327.0203 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Efforts to Promote Traditional Arts Urged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Culture Minister Liu
Zhongde today stressed the importance of passing down Chinese
cultural and artistic traditions, and also accepting new ideas
from abroad.
</P>
<P>
"If the Chinese nation does not continue to carry forward and
develop the arts of its own, it will lose independence in the
cultural and artistic field and become a retainer of foreign
culture, particularly Western culture. That would be very
dangerous," Liu told 300 celebrities gathered here to mark the
centenary of the birth of Pan Tianshou, a master of traditional
Chinese painting.
</P>
<P>
Pan is known for his adhering to traditional artistic
values. He considered Chinese painting and Western painting as two
peaks, representing different cultural systems, that stand facing
each other.
</P>
<P>
Pan is honored in China's arts circle as Picasso is honored in
the West.
</P>
<P>
Chinese President Jiang Zemin visited Pan's exhibits yesterday,
and praised the artist's spirit.
</P>
<P>
Liu said that artists should actively learn from "progressive
and fine Western arts."
</P>
<P>
Another senior official, Gao Zhanxiang, noted that Pan was a
loyal patriot who always shouldered great social responsibility.
</P>
<P>
Traditional Chinese painting is a time-honored art in the
country. Its symbolic and abstract language has attracted fans in
Asia and some other Western countries, and masterpieces are
auctioned for millions of US dollars on the international market.
</P>
<P>
The introduction of some Western techniques is the latest trend
in the art, which traditionally uses brushes and ink to draw
pictures on a special kind of white paper, known as "Xuanzhi" in
Chinese.
</P>
<P>
Prof. Pan was among the first group of artists to bring
traditional Chinese painting into universities in the 1920s. He
was tortured and later died at age 75 during the Cultural
Revolution (1966-76).
</P>
<P>
However, thousands of his works have been preserved as a legacy
of the nation.
</P>
<P>
State Councillor Li Tieying attended today's gathering. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
