<HEADLINE> Overseas-Funded Enterprises in Shanghai Perform Well </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Foreign-funded enterprises in
Shanghai, China's largest industrial center, performed well in
1996 with the combined profit rising by 20 percent to reach 12.2
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The combined turnover of the 9,157 operational foreign-funded
firms in Shanghai climbed to 207.2 billion yuan last year, a 48.5
percent increase.
</P>
<P>
Industrial firms built with overseas investment have become the
mainstay, generating a total output value of 165.7 billion yuan
last year, accounting for 32.6 percent of the city's total. Their
profits came to 10.4 billion yuan, accounting for 85 percent of
total of the local foreign-funded firms.
</P>
<P>
Foreign firms involved in the service sector reported a fast
growth in recent years. Last year, the service trade gained a
sales revenue of 28.3 billion yuan, 50 percent over the previous
year's volume. Commerce ranked first in sale's profit followed by
the hotel industry. 
</P>
