<HEADLINE> 7 Vacationers Killed in Guatemalan Bus Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Seven people died and 47
others were injured when a passenger bus collided with a pickup
truck today in Guatemala.
</P>
<P>
Five adults and a child were killed at the scene while a
seventh victim died in hospital, according to reports reaching
here.
</P>
<P>
The bus, packed with more than 60 Easter week vacationers, hit
the truck and went over an embankment into a steep ravine, the
reports quoted emergency workers as saying.
</P>
<P>
Rescue teams from the Guatemalan capital and four neighboring
municipalities used ropes and cables to bring up survivors and
bodies from 50 meters below the ravine.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred on the day of heaviest domestic travel by
Guatemalans during Easter Week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
