<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 26 (Xinhua) -- At least 39 young men have
been found dead at the scene of an apparent mass suicide in
western United States.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here quoted a San Diego sheriff's deputy as
saying that the men, all 18 to 24 years old, were dressed in
matching dark pants and dark tennis shoes.
</P>
<P>
No blood, signs of struggle or trauma were found at the scene
in Rancho Santa Fe, 32 kilometers north of San Diego, California.
</P>
<P>
Investigators believe it was a mass suicide "due to the number
of people involved".
</P>
<P>
The cause of death has not been determined. Blood samples from
the bodies were sent to a hospital for tests. 
