<HEADLINE> Investments in Philippine Ecozones Balloon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Investments in the Philippine
economic zones ballooned to 57 billion pesos (2.2 billion U.S.
dollars) in the first quarter of this year, up by 714 percent from
the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Philippine Economic Zone Authority Director-General Lilia de
Lima was quoted by today's local press as saying that the amount
is already equivalent to 76 percent of the whole year's target.
</P>
<P>
De Lima said the investments were generated from new and
expansion projects in the zones, adding that this year's target
could be exceeded before the third quarter.
</P>
<P>
The country now has 54 economic zones with 553 foreign
enterprises operating inside. Last year, exports from these zones
reached 6.5 billion U.S. dollars, an increase of 54 percent over
1995.
</P>
<P>
As the zones play an important role in the development of the
country's national economy, Philippine President Fidel Ramos
recently ordered the establishment of 15 more across the country.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
