<HEADLINE> Prodi Determined to Join Single Currency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Italy is determined to qualify and
join the launch of the European single currency, Italian Prime
Minister Romano Prodi told visiting German businessmen today.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with the delegation from the Federation of
German Industries, led by its chairman Hans Olaf Henkel, Prodi
explained his government's strategy for promoting structural
economic reforms as well as his government's determination to join
the single currency mechanism. They discussed plans for reforming
welfare in the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Treasury Minister Carlo Azeglio Ciampi, talking with the the
German delegation, stressed that the Italian economy was in a
position to support the stability of the euro.
</P>
<P>
Henkel expressed his support for Italian participation in the
euro "as soon as possible".
</P>
<P>
The two sides also agreed on the needs for urgent structural
budgetary measures, to lighten the fiscal and contributory burden
on business and to promote flexibility in the labor market.
</P>
