<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qiao Shi Holds Talks With French Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of the Standing
Committee of China's National People's Congress (NPC), today
briefed French Prime Minister Alain Juppe about Hong Kong and the
construction of a legal system in China.
</P>
<P>
At the beginning of the meeting held in the French Prime
Minister's Office, Juppe expressed his deep condolences over the
death of Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
He said that the French government attaches special importance
to developing relations with China and is closely following the
situation of development in China.
</P>
<P>
Qiao conveyed the regards from Chinese Premier Li Peng to Juppe
and praised Juppe for the contributions he has made to developing
friendly relations between France and China.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said that China will inherit the will of Deng Xiaoping and
carry forward the cause of socialist construction with Chinese
characteristics pioneered by Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that China will never change the basic policies
formulated during the lifetime of Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
On the return of Hong Kong to China on July 1, 1997, Qiao
recalled that after the 1984 Sino-British Joint Declaration on the
future of Hong Kong, China adopted the Basic Law of Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) in 1990.
</P>
<P>
He said that after the return of Hong Kong to China, no local
law of Hong Kong should go against the Basic Law of HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, China will also strictly observe the Basic Law in
making its policies concerning Hong Kong, he said.
</P>
<P>
Qiao Shi said that the 5th Plenary Session of the 8th NPC
recently adopted a resolution on Hong Kong on the basis of a
report by the Preparatory Committee for the Establishment of the
HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
He said that in the next 50 years or even longer, China will
strictly observe the Basic Law of the HKSAR, implement the policy
of "One Country, Two Systems" and let Hong Kong people run their
own affairs.
</P>
<P>
Qiao pointed out that the return of Hong Kong to China will
benefit Hong Kong's long-term prosperity and stability as well as
the development of China.
</P>
<P>
He also said that China will protect foreign interests in Hong
Kong according to the law.
</P>
<P>
On the construction of a legal system in China, Qiao said that
to rule the country in line with law and build a socialist state
with a legal system is the ultimate goal of China.
</P>
<P>
He said that China is wasting no time in its construction of a
legal system, and pointed out that the amendments made recently by
the NPC on China's criminal code have made it a totally new
criminal code for the country.
</P>
<P>
"If we keep on making unremitting efforts in the construction
of a legal system, we will surely attain our aim of building a
socialist state with a legal system," he said.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Qiao also briefed Juppe on the economic
development in China.
</P>
<P>
Qiao arrived here Tuesday on a six-day official visit to
France. 
</P>
</TEXT>
