<HEADLINE> U.S. President Appoints Health Panel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 26 (Xinhua) -- United States President Bill
Clinton today named a 32-member commission to protect the rights
and health care of consumers.
</P>
<P>
The Health Care Quality Commission will be co-chaired by Health
Secretary Donna Shalala and acting Labor Secretary Cynthia Metzler.
</P>
<P>
Clinton said it is urgent for the commission "to find ways to
ensure quality and to ensure that the rights of consumers are
protected".
</P>
<P>
He said he remained "committed to improving our health care
system, to making it more affordable, more accessible while
preserving its high quality." 
</P>
</TEXT>
