<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-British Joint Venture for Diesel Engines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, March 27 (Xinhua) -- An agreement was signed Tuesday
to establish a new Sino-British joint venture to build 50,000
diesel engines in China annually.
</P>
<P>
The new company, Perkins Engines (Tianjin) Co. Ltd., is jointly
funded by Varity Perkins of Britain and the Tianjin Power
Equipment Plant, with the British side holding 60 percent of the
stake.
</P>
<P>
The company will produce Perkins-brand phasers with four- and
six-liter capacity, and different kinds of engines. The company
will be able to produce 50,000 Perkins-branded engines
annually before 2001, ranging from 80 to 210 horse power. As a
long-term goal, the joint venture is expected to have an annual
production capacity of 120,000 engines.
</P>
<P>
The Tianjin Power Equipment Plant, founded in 1935, produced
China's first diesel engine. The factory now has over 7,000
workers.
</P>
<P>
Varity Perkins Co. Ltd. is a subsidiary of Lucus Varity Company
which has won a reputation for its manufacture of auto, diesel
engines and aerospace products. Varity Perkins Co. Ltd., with
4,500 employees, now supplies the world market with 300,000 diesel
and natural gas engines a year.
</P>
<P>
The parent company has also made investments in Xiamen, east
China's Fujian Province, and in the China No.1 Automobile
Manufacturing Company in Changchun, capital of east China's Jilin
Province, and in the No.2 Automobile Company of central China's
Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
With the goal for producing engines in China ranging from five
to 500 horse power, Lucus Varity Company also plans to set up more
joint ventures in China, sources said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
