<HEADLINE> Venezuelan Petroleum Company Forms Environment Panel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Venezuela's state-owned petroleum
company, PDVSA, has created a committee to mobilize efforts across
the industrial sector for environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
Petroleum companies in the country are joining the committee,
said a PDVSA communique released today.
</P>
<P>
The committee's main objective, the communique said, is to
facilitate the exchange of technical information and the search
for common positions among its members in face of certain problems.
</P>
<P>
Such a committee will benefit the country and companies in the
petroleum sector, as they will work together for the conservation
of the environment and industrial hygiene and safety, it said.
</P>
<P>
The committee will also be a channel of communication among its
members, the local governments and non-governmental organizations,
it added. 
</P>
