<HEADLINE> No More Foreign Cars for Russian Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
today signed a presidential decree stipulating that government
bodies are not allowed to fund the purchase of foreign cars after
April 1.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by new First Deputy Prime Minister, Boris
Nemtsov, at a news conference.
</P>
<P>
Nemtsov said there would be no more foreign cars at state
expense for state officials, and foreign cars at present used by
government officials would be auctioned off gradually.
</P>
<P>
Political analysts here said this showed that Yeltsin was keen
to cut government spending. 
</P>
