<HEADLINE> Costa Rican Legislator Calls for Diplomatic Ties With China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, March 26 (Xinhua) -- A legislator of the ruling
National Liberation Party said today it is advantageous for Costa
Rica to have diplomatic ties with the People's Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
"It is time for Costa Rica to think about establishing
relations with China," deputy Otton Solis told reporters at the
end of a Chinese delegation's three-day visit to the country.
</P>
<P>
"China, with political stability and economic prosperity, is
one of the seven largest economies in the world and its future is
promising," said Solis, who is also an economist.
</P>
<P>
With China's opening up and economic reform, he asserted, the
country's prosperity "is guaranteed".
</P>
<P>
He stressed Costa Rica should re-evaluate its ties with China.
</P>
<P>
"Our economic interests should be supreme. We cannot allow our
orientation of political nature to prevail in international
relations," the legislator added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
