<HEADLINE> Qiao Shi Stresses Sino-French Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese National People's
Congress (NPC) Chairman Qiao Shi said here today that China is
willing to enhance cooperation with France and together with
France to contribute to the building of a new international
political order.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a dinner given in his honor by French Senate
President Rene Monory, Qiao said that there is no fundamental
conflict of interests between China and France.
</P>
<P>
As permanent members of the Security Council of the United
Nations, Qiao said, the two countries bare the responsibility for
the peace and development in the world and they share same or
similar views over many important international issues.
</P>
<P>
Since China and France established diplomatic relations more
than 30 years ago, bilateral relations have developed gradually,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said he hoped his visit to France will enhance
understanding and friendship between the two countries, strengthen
cooperation between them and make contribution to durable and
stable friendship and cooperation geared toward the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Monory said that China's economy has grown very fast
and China plays a more and more important role on the
international arena.
</P>
<P>
Relations between the two countries are good, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The French Senate president said: "We will further strengthen
exchanges between the two countries. Only by this way, we can
deepen each other's understanding and upstage the relations
between our two countries." 
</P>
</TEXT>
