<HEADLINE> FAO Aid For Sri Lanka's Aquaculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 27 (Xinhua) -- The United Nation's Food and
Agriculture Organization (FAO) has provided 311,000 US dollars in
aid for Sri Lanka's aquaculture development, according to the
Finance Ministry today.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said the aid is to be used for a project to
increase fish production in inland and coastal water bodies.
</P>
<P>
Training will be provided in pond management, fish roe
production, disease control, fish transportation and distribution
and reservoir fisheries management.
</P>
<P>
An information base will be set up to study coastal and other
water resources in the country, it said.  
</P>
