<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mob Destroys Shops, Offices in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Seven people were injured last
night in a riot in Pekalongan of Indonesia's central Java province
and scores of rioters were arrested, the Indonesia Times reported
today.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of people ran amok, demolishing shops, offices and
public utilities during the midnight riot in the coastal city,
said the report.
</P>
<P>
The mob also set four motorcycles and one car ablaze, but there
have been no reports of casualties.
</P>
<P>
The rioters burned tires and firewood, blocking the street
leading to a boarding school where a sermon by a leading Jakarta
preacher was scheduled to take place.
</P>
<P>
This was the second riot in two days in the city. On Monday,
hundreds of people stormed a stage with stones and Molotov
cocktails. They also burned flags and banners.
</P>
<P>
The local military authorities said the riots were caused by a
"verbal war" between dissatisfied people and local authorities
over the procedures for hoisting political parties' flags at any
gathering or ceremony.
</P>
<P>
A military officer said the three political parties -- the
ruling Golkar, the United Development Party (PPP) and the
Indonesian Democratic Party (PDI) have agreed not to hoist party
flags when they hold any gathering or ceremony.
</P>
<P>
However, yellow flags (Golkar flag) were hoisted along the
street prior to the sermon which was expected to attended by "one
million followers" and then the yellow flags were replaced by
green flags (PPP flag).
</P>
<P>
Tensions among the supporters of the three political parties
which are preparing for the May 29 general election, are predicted
to mount, reports said.
</P>
<P>
The three parties are vying for 425 seats of the House of
Representatives in the May election during which more than 120
million people are eligible to vote.
</P>
<P>
"The military authority has arrested scores of rioters," said
the central Java military commander, Major General Subagyo H.S.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
