<HEADLINE> North China Province Helps Resettlement of Dam Area County </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Hebei Province has announced
plans to help with the resettlement of local residents of Fengdu
County, in northwest China's Chongqing Municipality, who have been
affected by the Three Gorge Dam project.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, the province so far has signed
agreements with the northwestern county for 19 economic and
technological cooperation projects, involving a total investment
of 64.7 million yuan. Hebei will contribute 8.29 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the province has also started six public
welfare programs in Fengdu and provided free financial aid in kind
and capital, with a value of 6.2 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Fengdu, known for its rich folklore, is one of the first group
of areas to be inundated when the damming for the Three Gorges
Water Control project begins on the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
The county is expected to complete the resettlement work and
build a new county seat on the southern bank of the Yangtze before
the year 2003, in accordance with construction plan for the
gigantic water control project, to be built in the Three Gorges on
the middle reaches of the Yangtze.
</P>
<P>
Appreciating the support, Ye Liansong, governor of Hebei
province, said that Hebei had designated ten cities, ten
profitable firms and 20 government institutions to help carry out
the detailed resettlement process.
</P>
<P>
The province has also established a special fund to support the
program. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
