<HEADLINE> Export of Chinese Durable Goods up in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 27 (Xinhua) -- China exported 27.5 billion US
dollars-worth of household electrical appliances last year, up
18.5 percent from the 1995 figure, according to Business News.
</P>
<P>
Electric fans were the biggest export item, with a total export
of 67 million units, netting an output value of 650 million US
dollars.
</P>
