<HEADLINE> China Practices Certification System for Medical Equipment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 27 (Xinhua) -- China is starting a certification
system for medical equipment aiming to strengthen control over
product quality, according to today's "China Daily".
</P>
<P>
The China Quality Certification Center for Medical Devices,
under the State Pharmaceutical Administration (SPA), will organize
experts to test the products. The label of "Chinese medical
device" (CMD) will be granted to equipment meeting international
standards, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
Sample inspections will be carried out every six months on CMD
products. The certificate will be revoked if the enterprise fails
to maintain its quality level, the paper quoted Bu Qicheng,
director of SPA's Medical Device Administration Department, as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Five medical device manufacturers, which obtained CMD
certificates in Beijing Wednesday, became the first to pass the
national scrutiny.
</P>
<P>
All these enterprises have established a quality control system
and manufacture products in line with international technical
standards. They also carry out occupational training for their
employees.  
</P>
</TEXT>
