<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Xi'an, the capital city of
landlocked Shaanxi Province in northwest China, is now determined
to regain its old glory as one of the country's earliest open
cities.
</P>
<P>
The former capital of 12 Chinese feudal dynasties will grab the
opportunity provided by the central government's decision to
accelerate the economic development in the central and western
areas of the country, said today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
To boost its opening drive, the city has chosen more than 30
projects seeking foreign cooperation and investment.
</P>
<P>
The projects cover electronics, machinery, raw materials, light
industry, textiles, tourism, commodity circulation, finance and
insurance, information and consultancy, unban infrastructure and
public facilities.
</P>
<P>
The city will also hold a large international trade fair from
September 12 to 17 this year.
</P>
<P>
Although geographically disadvantaged compared to coastal
cities, Xi'an boasts a solid industrial base, strong technological
research forces, rich tourism resources and a well-built air, rail
and highway network, said the newspaper.  
