<HEADLINE> Air China Tianjin Branch to Open Three New Air Routes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Air China Tianjin branch will
open three new air routes connecting this north municipality with
four other cities in China.
</P>
<P>
An air route linking Tianjin with Guilin, a scenic city in south
China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, via Nanjing, capital of
east China's Jiangsu province, will be opened on March 31.
</P>
<P>
Another route connecting Tianjin with Chongqing, the
newly-established municipality in the southwestern part of the
country, will be opened on April 2.
</P>
<P>
Flights between Tianjin and the port city of Ningbo in east
China's Zhejiang Province will be opened on April 8.
</P>
<P>
The three routes will see two flights a week.
</P>
<P>
The branch will then have 15 air routes starting from Tianjin
to 16 other Chinese cities. 
</P>
