<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Auto Afficionado Assembles Asia's Longest Car </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, March 27 (Xinhua) -- An auto enthusiast in northeast
China's Liaoning Province has designed and made an 11.2-meter-long
luxury vehicle, hailed by the local press as the longest car in
Asia.
</P>
<P>
Shang Yuecheng, 38, an experienced chauffeur and amateur auto
afficionado, envisioned his own car-making project five years ago.
</P>
<P>
The limousine, dubbed "King of Asia," became a reality after
Shang and five other auto technicians spent two months and 200,000
yuan (24,390 US dollars) on the work.
</P>
<P>
"It is really tough to tackle the problems such as building a
weight-supporting structure for such a car," Shang said.
</P>
<P>
The colossal four-door vehicle is 11.2 meters in length and
1.94 meters wide. The distance between the front and rear wheels
is 10.18 meters. Road tests show that the car can carry a maximum
weight of six tons while maintaining a speed of 100 kilometers per
hour.
</P>
<P>
Witnesses said that the luxurious interior of the sedan is a
match for the big-name brands, as it has a full range of
amenities, including a mini-bar, an air-conditioner, a color TV
set, a refrigerator, a mobile phone, a VCD player and genuine
leather seats.
</P>
<P>
The maximum seating capacity is ten people, "enough for a
small meeting," he added.
</P>
<P>
A local TV station searched all available references and
labeled the car longest in Asia.
</P>
<P>
The car has caused a sensation in surrounding areas. Several
deluxe hotels in Beijing, Shanghai, and Dalian have already shown
strong interest in buying the car. But Shang has another idea in
mind.
</P>
<P>
"I expect to present the car to Mr. Tung Chee-Hwa, the first
chief executive of Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, when
Hong Kong returns to the motherland," he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
