<DOCNO> XIE19970327.0288 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sampras Advances in Lipton Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Pete Sampras advanced to the
semifinals of the 4.45 million US dollars Lipton Championships on
Wednesday in a walkover after a freak accident befell his
quarterfinal round opponent.
</P>
<P>
Hendrik Dreekman of Germany sprained an ankle walking back to
his hotel in downtown Miami on Tuesday evening and was forced to
withdraw from the quarterfinal match.
</P>
<P>
The day's real drama was reserved for the women's quarterfinal
between third-seeded Jana Novotna of the Czech Republic and
eighth-seeded Iva Majoli of Croatia. Novotna eventually won the
two hour and 24-minute cliff-hanger 6-3, 2-6, 7-6 (9-7.)
</P>
<P>
Novotna, ranked fourth and Majoli, ranked 10th, battled evenly
in the first two sets.
</P>
<P>
In the decisive third set, Novotna jumped to a 3-1 lead, but
twice failed to serve out the match at 5-4 and 6-5, which sent the
set to a tiebreaker.
</P>
<P>
Novotna missed her first match point at 6-5, slicing an
approach shot wide. At 7-6, she faltered again with a wild
forehand error. Instead, it was Majoli, steady throughout the
match, who gave away the third match point with a smash wide.
</P>
<P>
Dreekman's withdrawal followed a curious tournament tradition
of players suffering strange accidents and injuries at The Lipton.
</P>
<P>
The most notorious occurred in 1989 when Thomas Muster of
Austria was hit by a car outside his hotel in Miami, the night
before his final with Ivan Lendl. The injury took Muster off the
tour for six months.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Goran Ivanisevic defaulted in the final with Andre
Agassi after three games, suffering from a stiff neck, a problem
he had sustained during the night.
</P>
<P>
In 1994, Sampras had delayed the start of the final for two
hours with stomach problems, before defeating Agassi for the title.
</P>
<P>
Boris Becker claimed food poisoning from fish before
withdrawing from the event in 1989.
</P>
<P>
In 1993, Becker advanced to the third round without playing a
match when second-round opponent, Gianluca Pozzi, was rushed to
the hospital with appendicitis. Becker withdrew with the flu one
round later. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970327.0289 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-27 </DATE_TIME>
