<HEADLINE> Qiao Shi Expresses Wish to Develop Ties with </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, the chairman of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC) of
China, today had a meeting with the president of the French
Senate, Rene Monory, in the latter's office in the Luxembourg
Palace.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said that both the NPC and the French Parliament are
playing an important role in the political life of their own
countries, and that the relationship between the NPC and the
French Parliament is an important part of the overall Sino-French
relations.
</P>
<P>
"My visit is the first by a NPC chairman of China to France. I
hope that this visit will be able to attain the goal of further
strengthening Sino-French relations and increasing friendly
exchanges and cooperation between the NPC and the French
Parliament," he said.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed his hope that the NPC and the French
Parliament will continue to strengthen contacts and further
develop bilateral relations of friendly cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said that both China and France cherish a tradition of
safeguarding their national independence, and share common views
on many important international issues.
</P>
<P>
He said that China and France have a strong complementary
relationship with each other when carrying out economic
cooperations, and trade cooperations between the two countries
have great potentials for development.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said that while the world is moving toward multipolarism,
it will benefit not only China and France, but also world peace,
stability and development, if the two countries develop a
relationship of mutual respect, equality and mutual benefit which
is oriented toward the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
He also praised Monory for having contributed to the
development of Sino-French relations and the role he played in
realizing the normalization of the relations between China and
France a few years ago.
</P>
<P>
Monory welcomed Qiao to visit France, and expressed his belief
that the visit will further strengthen the relationship of
friendly cooperation between France and China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
