<HEADLINE> Qiao Shi, de Charette Stress Sino-French Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 26 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, the chairman of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress of China,
today had a meeting with French Foreign Minister Herve de Charette
at the Lutetia Hotel of Paris where Qiao was staying.
</P>
<P>
De Charette told Qiao that France pays great importance to
developing relations with China, and is willing to develop trade
relations with China.
</P>
<P>
He said that France is happy that President Jacques Chirac will
pay a state visit to China in May.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said that President Chirac is an old friend of the Chinese
people, and expressed his belief that his visit to China will
greatly push forward the development of Sino-French friendly
relations.
</P>
<P>
Qiao also said that both China and France will win huge
benefits if China can take advantage of France's advanced science
and technology, while France makes use of China's abundant labor
force and huge market.
</P>
<P>
Both of them agreed that the world is moving toward
multipolarism, that the international order cannot be dominated by
one single power, and that the national sovereignty and
independence of all countries should be fully respected.
</P>
<P>
They also agreed that China and France should intensify
consultation and cooperation with each other in international
affairs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
