<HEADLINE> French FM Expresses Grave Concern over Situation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 26 (Xinhua) -- French Foreign Minister Herve de
Charette today shared with Palestinian Minister of Culture Abed
Rabbo their "very grave concern over the generalized blockade of
all discussion" between Israel and Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
"There is a grave worry among all those who are attached to
the peace process. There are not several ways toward peace. There
is not but one: pursue and resume the negotiations in conformity
to the agreements of Oslo and Taba," said de Charette following a
45-minute meeting with Rabbo.
</P>
<P>
He said, "It is in the respect of the promise given that there
is peace. It is in the resumption of the peace process that there
is security. Otherwise, there are grounds for being worried."
</P>
<P>
Rabbo told de Charette that there exists "great worry among
Palestinians over the present situation," and that the economic
situation in the Palestinian territories are "catastrophic."
</P>
<P>
De Charette also expressed his worry that tension might rise
again in southern Lebanon between Israel and the Hezbollah
guerrillas.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister today also inaugurated at the Institute du
Monde Arabe in Paris two exhibitions under the theme of
"Palestinian Spring."
</P>
<P>
De Charette said when visiting the exhibitions that "Jerusalem
should remain the city of pluralism and marriage of
civilizations." 
</P>
</TEXT>
